South African bonds were stable at midday on Tuesday amid thin trade because of the holiday season.At 11.29am, the R186 was bid at 9.00% from 8.96% previously while the R207 was bid at 8.22%&sbquo; from 8.185% previously.The rand, which local bonds often track, was slightly weaker against the dollar as investors sought safe-haven assets after a suspected terrorist attack in Germany and the assassination of the Russian ambassador to Turkey, Andrei Karlov, which rattled international markets.TreasuryOne head of dealing Wichard Cilliers said it seemed markets were "not too shaken by recent events" although the rand opened slightly weaker in the morning.&nbsp;